---js
const eleventyNavigation = {
	key: "Home",
	order: 1
};

const numberOfLatestPostsToShow = 10;
---

<div class="intro-section">
    <p>
        Hey, I&#8217;m ldstephens. I&#8217;ve been writing online since the late
        1990s. Previous versions of this site have been on Bear, Write.as, and,
        before that, WordPress. For now, this is my little corner of the web
        where I share whatever&#8217;s on my mind: stories, random thoughts, and
        the occasional rant.
    </p>
    <p>
        Could be great, could be a mess. Either way, stick around. Or
        don&#8217;t. It&#8217;s your call.
    </p>
</div>

{% set postsCount = collections.posts | length %} {% set latestPostsCount =
postsCount | min(numberOfLatestPostsToShow) %}
<h1>
    {{ latestPostsCount }} Most Recent Post{% if latestPostsCount != 1 %}s{%
    endif %}
</h1>

{% set postslist = collections.posts | head(-1 * numberOfLatestPostsToShow) %}
{% set postslistCounter = postsCount %} {% include "postslist.njk" %} {% set
morePosts = postsCount - numberOfLatestPostsToShow %} {% if morePosts > 0 %}
<p>
    {{ morePosts }} more post{% if morePosts != 1 %}s{% endif %} can be found in
    <a href="blog.njk">the archive</a>.
</p>
{% endif %} {# List every content page in the project #} {#
<ul>
    {%- for entry in collections.all %}
    <li>
        <a href="{{ entry.url }}"><code>{{ entry.url }}</code></a>
    </li>
    {%- endfor %}
</ul>
#}
